<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="1243" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="4.[138,1185,529,649]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1243">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Templeton" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[165,370,562,586]" class="Collembola" family="Orchesellidae" genus="Heteromurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="1243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis box="[165,370,562,586]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1243">Heteromurus nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a troglophilic species with holarctic distribution. It has been reported from numerous localities along the Italian peninsula (
<bibRefCitation author="Dallai R &amp; Malatesta E &amp; Ramellini P" box="[780,994,594,618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1243" pagination="33" refId="ref3418" refString="Dallai R, Malatesta E, Ramellini P. 1995. Apterygota: Collembola, Protura, Microcoryphia e Zygentoma (5 Thysanura s. l.), Diplura. In: Minelli A, Ruffo S, La Posta S, editors. Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana 33. Bologna: Calderini." type="book chapter" year="1995">Dallai et al. 1995</bibRefCitation>
) both from soil samples and caves (
<bibRefCitation author="Dallai R &amp; Malatesta E" box="[362,671,625,649]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1243" pagination="173 - 194" refId="ref3388" refString="Dallai R, Malatesta E. 1982. Collemboli cavernicoli italiani (Ricerche sui Collemboli XXVI). Lavori della Societa Italiana di Biogeografia 7: 173 - 194." type="journal article" year="1982">Dallai and Malatesta 1982</bibRefCitation>
) where it usually occurs as a typical element.
</paragraph>
